## New Space Setup
When starting a fresh DevSpace, the agent should:
1. Point AWS CLI to persisted credentials:
   ```bash
   export AWS_CONFIG_FILE=~/shared/.aws/config
   export AWS_SHARED_CREDENTIALS_FILE=~/shared/.aws/credentials
   ```
2. Clone the repo (requires GitHub token from user):
   ```bash
   git clone https://<TOKEN>@github.com/binhtq80/myapp-infra.git /workspace/myapp-infra
   ```
3. Run setup:
   ```bash
   ENV_FILE=~/shared/myapp-envs/<env>.sh ./scripts/setup-devspace.sh
   ```

### Persisted in ~/shared/ (survives DevSpace restarts)
- `~/shared/.aws/config` — AWS CLI config (profile names + regions)
- `~/shared/.aws/credentials` — AWS access keys
- `~/shared/myapp-envs/*.sh` — per-account environment configs
- `~/shared/myapp-context.md` — this file

