## Architecture Summary
Full-stack home device management app:
- Frontend: React 18 + Vite + TypeScript
- Backend: Node.js Lambda (CommonJS), single bundle packaging
- Infrastructure: CDK v2 TypeScript
- AI: Bedrock Claude Haiku (device recognition + energy tips + complexity classification)
- Auth: Cognito
- DB: DynamoDB (users, devices, device-energy, device-history, device-notes, device-favorites, feature-requests)

## RBAC Roles
| Role | Permissions |
|------|-------------|
| user | Submit requests, view devices, basic access |
| technical | Accept/override AI complexity classifications |
| product_manager | Approve/reject feature requests |
| admin | Manage user roles via Admin panel |

Bootstrap: `ENV_FILE=~/shared/myapp-envs/<env>.sh ./scripts/assign-role.sh <username> <role>`

## Automation Loop
- `./scripts/feature.sh` — CLI for submitting features and managing orchestrator
- `./scripts/orchestrator.sh` — background daemon that implements features via kiro-cli
- DynamoDB `claimedBy` field enables multi-DevSpace parallel processing
- Deploy routing: frontend-only → S3 sync (~30s), backend → Lambda update (~2min), infra → CDK Pipeline

## How to Resume Work
```bash
# 1. Read this file and README.md for context
cd /workspace/myapp-infra && ./scripts/feature.sh status
git log --oneline -10

# 2. Start orchestrator targeting your account
ENV_FILE=~/shared/myapp-envs/<env>.sh ./scripts/feature.sh start
```

